**Product 3 Image Display and Management System**

This system is designed to display and manage product images, specifically product3.jpg. The system will be built using HTML, CSS, and JS for the frontend, Core PHP for the backend, and MySQL/MariaDB for the database.

### Database Schema

The database schema will consist of a single table, `products`, with the following columns:

* `id` (primary key, auto-increment): unique identifier for each product
* `name`: name of the product
* `image`: path to the product image
* `description`: brief description of the product

```sql
CREATE TABLE products (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,
  name VARCHAR(255),
  image VARCHAR(255),
  description TEXT
);
```

### Frontend (HTML, CSS, JS)

The frontend will display the product image and provide a form to update the product information.

**index.html**
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Product 3 Image</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Product 3 Image</h1>
  <img id="product-image" src="images/product3.jpg" alt="Product 3 Image">
  <form id="update-form">
    <label for="name">Name:</label>
    <input type="text" id="name" name="name"><br><br>
    <label for="description">Description:</label>
    <textarea id="description" name="description"></textarea><br><br>
    <input type="submit" value="Update">
  </form>

  <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

**style.css**
```css
body {
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
}

#product-image {
  width: 50%;
  height: auto;
  margin: 20px;
}

#update-form {
  width: 50%;
  margin: 20px;
}

label {
  display: block;
  margin-bottom: 10px;
}

input, textarea {
  width: 100%;
  padding: 10px;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
  border: 1px solid #ccc;
}

input[type="submit"] {
  background-color: #4CAF50;
  color: #fff;
  padding: 10px 20px;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 5px;
  cursor: pointer;
}

input[type="submit"]:hover {
  background-color: #3e8e41;
}
```

**script.js**
```javascript
const updateForm = document.getElementById('update-form');
const productName = document.getElementById('name');
const productDescription = document.getElementById('description');

updateForm.addEventListener('submit', (e) => {
  e.preventDefault();
  const formData = new FormData();
  formData.append('name', productName.value);
  formData.append('description', productDescription.value);

  fetch('update-product.php', {
    method: 'POST',
    body: formData
  })
  .then((response) => response.json())
  .then((data) => console.log(data))
  .catch((error) => console.error(error));
});
```

### Backend (Core PHP)

The backend will handle the form submission and update the product information in the database.

**update-product.php**
```php
<?php
  $servername = "localhost";
  $username = "root";
  $password = "";
  $dbname = "products";

  // Create connection
  $conn = new mysqli($servername, $username, $password, $dbname);

  // Check connection
  if ($conn->connect_error) {
    die("Connection failed: " . $conn->connect_error);
  }

  if ($_SERVER["REQUEST_METHOD"] == "POST") {
    $name = $_POST['name'];
    $description = $_POST['description'];

    $sql = "UPDATE products SET name='$name', description='$description' WHERE id=3";

    if ($conn->query($sql) === TRUE) {
      echo "Product updated successfully";
    } else {
      echo "Error updating product: " . $conn->error;
    }
  }

  $conn->close();
?>
```

### Database Interaction (MySQL/MariaDB)

The database interaction will be handled by the Core PHP backend.

**products.php**
```php
<?php
  $servername = "localhost";
  $username = "root";
  $password = "";
  $dbname = "products";

  // Create connection
  $conn = new mysqli($servername, $username, $password, $dbname);

  // Check connection
  if ($conn->connect_error) {
    die("Connection failed: " . $conn->connect_error);
  }

  $sql = "SELECT * FROM products WHERE id=3";
  $result = $conn->query($sql);

  if ($result->num_rows > 0) {
    while($row = $result->fetch_assoc()) {
      echo "Name: " . $row["name"]. "<br>";
      echo "Image: " . $row["image"]. "<br>";
      echo "Description: " . $row["description"]. "<br>";
    }
  } else {
    echo "0 results";
  }

  $conn->close();
?>
```

This system provides a basic framework for displaying and managing product images, specifically product3.jpg. The frontend displays the product image and provides a form to update the product information. The backend handles the form submission and updates the product information in the database. The database interaction is handled by the Core PHP backend.